Finally, the Buffalo Filter smoke evacuator tubing is connected to 2 heat moisture exchange (HME) filters and placed under the drape to provide further air filtration (Figure 3
and Figure 4
). The reason for the multi-filter system is to attempt maximum efficiency in filtering viral particles. According to the respective manufacturers, Buffalo Filter has 4 stages of filtration that reportedly ensure 99.999% efficiency, down to 0.1-0.2 microns and HME filters provide bacterial and viral filtration exceeding 99.9%.
